{"title_page": "Aleris", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Aleris Corporation\n| logo                = Aleris Logo.svg\n| logo_size           = \n| logo_alt            = \n| logo_caption        = The company's logo\n| logo_padding        = \n| image               = Aleris corporate HQ 02 - Beachwood Ohio (29218109022).jpg\n| image_size          = \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       = The company's headquarters in [[Beachwood, Ohio]], in 2016\n| trading_name        = \n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{Lang|[code]|[name]}}. -->\n| romanized_name      = \n| former_name         = \n| type                = [[Subsidiary company|Subsidiary]]\n| traded_as           = \n| ISIN                = \n| ISIN2               = \n| industry            = [[Manufacturing]]\n| genre               = \n| fate                = \n| predecessor         = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor           = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded             = {{Start date and age|2004}}\n| founder             = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct             = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location         = \n| hq_location_city    = [[Beachwood, Ohio]]\n| hq_location_country = United States\n| num_locations       = \n| num_locations_year  = <!-- Year of num_locations data (if known) -->\n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = Sean Stack ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]])\n| products            = [[Aluminium|Aluminum]]\n| brands              = \n| production          = \n| production_year     = <!-- Year of production data (if known) -->\n| services            = \n| revenue             = \n| revenue_year        = <!-- Year of revenue data (if known) -->\n| operating_income    = \n| income_year         = <!-- Year of operating_income data (if known) -->\n| net_income          = <!-- or: | profit = -->\n| net_income_year     = <!-- or: | profit_year = --><!-- Year of net_income/profit data (if known) -->\n| aum                 = <!-- Only for financial-service companies -->\n| assets              = \n| assets_year         = <!-- Year of assets data (if known) -->\n| equity              = \n| equity_year         = <!-- Year of equity data (if known) -->\n| owner               = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| members             = \n| members_year        = <!-- Year of members data (if known) -->\n| num_employees       = 5,000\n| num_employees_year  = 2015\n| parent              = [[Hindalco Industries]]\n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = \n| module              = <!-- Used to embed other templates -->\n| ratio               = <!-- Basel III ratio, for BANKS ONLY -->\n| rating              = <!-- credit rating, for BANKS ONLY -->\n| website             = {{URL|aleris.com}}\n| footnotes           = \n}}\n'''Aleris Corporation''' (also '''Aleris Inc.''' or '''Aleris International Inc.''') is an [[Aluminium|aluminum]] rolled products [[Production (economics)|producer]], based in [[Beachwood, Ohio]]. The company had approximately 5,000 employees globally as of mid 2015.\n\nOn 15 April 2020, Aleris Corporation was acquired by [[Hindalco Industries]] subsidiary Novelis Inc. for $2.8 billion. With the deal closure, Hindalco is now one of the world\u2019s largest aluminium makers and Novelis' entered into the high-end aerospace segment<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/hindalco-closes-2-8-billion-acquisition-of-us-based-aleris-corp-11586876784438.html|title=Hindalco closes $2.8-billion acquisition of US-based Aleris Corp|last=Thomas|first=Tanya|date=2020-04-14|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Corporate affairs==\nAleris is an [[Aluminium|aluminum]] rolled products [[Production (economics)|producer]], based in [[Beachwood, Ohio]], a suburb of [[Cleveland]].<ref name=\"Suttell\">{{cite news |last1=Suttell |first1=Scott |title=Aleris Inc. names new CEO |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20150713/NEWS/150719954/aleris-inc-names-new-ceo |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |publisher=[[Crain Communications]] |date=July 13, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Barman\">{{cite news |first1=Arijit |last1=Barman |first2=Vatsala |last2=Gaur |title=Hindalco weighing bid to acquire Aleris Corp of US |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/company/deals/hindalco-weighing-bid-to-acquire-aleris-corp-of-us/articleshow/61094708.cms |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Economic Times]] |publisher=[[The Times Group]] |date=October 16, 2017 |oclc=61311680}}</ref> The [[privately held company]] had approximately 5,000 employees overall, as of mid 2015, around 200 of which are based in [[Northeast Ohio]], including a manufacturing facility in [[Uhrichsville, Ohio]].<ref name=\"Suttell\"/><ref name=\"Pledger\">{{cite news |last1=Pledger |first1=Marcia |title=Reinvention: How Beachwood-based Aleris went from bankruptcy to expanding worldwide |url=https://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2015/02/reinvention_how_beachwood-base.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Plain Dealer]] |publisher=[[Advance Publications]] |date=February 9, 2015}}</ref> Aleris has [[private equity]] owners, including [[Apollo Global]] and [[Oaktree Capital Management]].<ref name=\"Suttell\"/><ref name=\"Pooley\">{{cite news |last1=Pooley |first1=Cat Rutter |title=Chinese aluminium entrepreneur abandons $2.3bn attempt to buy Aleris |url=https://www.ft.com/content/9138d8d2-aeee-3f98-a77b-052aa4fd2bc7 |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |date=November 13, 2017 |issn=0307-1766}}</ref>\n\nSteve Demetriou served as the first [[chairman]] and [[chief executive officer]] (CEO).<ref name=\"Suttell\"/><ref name=Pledger/> Sean Stack became CEO and joined the [[board of directors]] in mid 2015. Scott Graves became a non-executive chairman of Aleris' board at the same time.<ref name=\"Suttell\"/>\n\n==History==\nAleris was established in 2004,<ref name=\"Suttell\"/> the result of a merger between an [[Aluminium recycling|aluminum recycling]] company and an aluminum rolled products company.<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris operated as a [[portfolio company]] of [[Texas Pacific Group]],<ref name=\"Wabash\">{{cite news |title=Aleris to buy aluminum producer |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20070705/FREE/70705001/aleris-to-buy-aluminum-producer |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |date=July 5, 2007}}</ref> and expanded via acquisitions during its early history. The company acquired [[Corus Group]]'s aluminum [[extrusion]] and rolling businesses for approximately $894 million (\u20ac700 million) in 2006,<ref name=\"Buys\">{{cite news |title=Aleris Buys Aluminium Assets from Corus |url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2006/05/24/aleris-buys-aluminium-assets-from-corus/ |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |date=May 24, 2006 |issn=0362-4331 |oclc=1645522}}</ref> and Wabash Alloys for an undisclosed amount in 2007.<ref name=Wabash/> Following the Corus acquisition, Aleris had approximately 8,800 employees and more than 40 manufacturing facilities globally.<ref name=Buys/> \n\nIn February 2009, the [[United States Department of Justice|Department of Justice]] filed suit against the company, alleging that 15 of its plants had violated the [[Clean Air Act (United States)|Clean Air Act]] by emission of pollutants. Aleris settled the suit with the government in August 2009, and agreed to pay a $4.6 million fine and spend an additional $4.2 million on new pollution controls at its plants.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2009/08/aluminum_recycler_aleris_inter.html | title=Aluminum recycler Aleris International Inc. to pay $4.6 million EPA fine | first=Frank | last=Bentayou | date=August 5, 2009 | work=[[The Plain Dealer]] | location=Cleveland, Ohio | accessdate=June 26, 2018}}</ref> The [[financial crisis of 2007\u20132008]] and [[Great Recession]] caused significant downturns in production, and Aleris experienced a 40 percent volume decline during 2008\u20132009.<ref name=Pledger/> In 2009, the company filed for [[Chapter 11, Title 11, United States Code|Chapter 11]] bankruptcy,<ref name=\"Pledger\"/> and Apollo, Oaktree Capital, and [[Sankaty Advisors]] became owners in 2010.<ref name=Pooley/><ref name=\"Reorganization\">{{cite news |title=Update 1-Aleris reorganization plan confirmed by court |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/aleris/update-1-aleris-reorganization-plan-confirmed-by-court-idUSSGE64C0KT20100513 |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |publisher=Reuters |date=May 13, 2010}}</ref> Aleris stabilized its financial position and significantly reduced debt. The company also invested in its facilities, building a new aerospace plate mill in China during the early 2010s, finishing a $70 million expansion of its facility in [[Duffel]] (2013),<ref name=\"Opens\">{{cite news |last1=Schoenberger |first1=Robert |title=Aleris International opens new aluminum mill in Belgium |url=https://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2013/03/aleris_international_opens_new.html |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |date=March 15, 2013 |work=The Plain Dealer}}</ref> and improving its plant in [[Ashville, Ohio]], in 2014.<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris acquired Nichols Aluminum and its production facilities in [[Davenport, Iowa]], [[Decatur, Alabama]], and [[Lincolnshire, Illinois]], for $110 million cash in 2014.<ref name=\"Berry\">{{cite news |last1=Berry |first1=Lucy |title=Aleris purchases Nichols Aluminum, which operates Decatur plant, for $110 million cash |url=https://www.al.com/business/index.ssf/2014/04/aleris_purchases_nichols_alumi.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Birmingham News]] |publisher=Advance Publications |date=April 1, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"DeWitt\">{{cite news |last1=DeWitt |first1=Jennifer |title=Aleris to aquire Nichols Aluminum from Quanex |url=https://qctimes.com/business/aleris-to-aquire-nichols-aluminum-from-quanex/article_15749d1c-06de-5f67-8b34-b98767c8b1c6.html |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |work=[[Quad-City Times]] |publisher=Lee Enterprises |date=February 10, 2014}}</ref> The aluminum finishing plant in Decatur was closed before the end of the year to streamline operations. Aleris had more than 40 production facilities in North America, Europe, and Asia, as of October 2014.<ref name=\"Closure\">{{cite news |last1=Berry |first1=Lucy |title=Aleris International announces Nichols Aluminum plant closure, 95 job cuts in Decatur |url=https://www.al.com/business/index.ssf/2014/10/aleris_international_announces.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Birmingham News]] |publisher=Advance Publications |date=October 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, the company focused on selling its extrusion and recycling businesses, and planned to raise approximately $600 million in capital. The divestitures decreased the number of employees to around 5,000.<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris abandoned plans to complete an [[initial public offering]] in 2015.<ref name=Pooley/><ref>{{cite news |title=Update 1-Private equity-backed aluminum processor Aleris scraps IPO plan |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/aleris-ipo/update-1-private-equity-backed-aluminum-processor-aleris-scraps-ipo-plan-idUSL4N0VF79320150205 |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |publisher=Reuters |date=February 5, 2015}}</ref> The company had approximately 7,000 employees in the U.S., Europe, and China at the time, including approximately 340 in Uhrichsville and 250 in [[Greater Cleveland]].<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris was also among the largest aluminum [[Sheet metal|sheet]] suppliers for [[semi-trailer]]s, and the leading aluminum sheet supplier for the U.S. residential construction industry.<ref name=Pledger/> The company increased production as the [[automotive industry]] began using more aluminum than steel.<ref name=Pledger/><ref name=\"Expand\">{{cite news |last1=Cohen |first1=Luc |title=Aleris may expand capacity in Europe for aluminum sheet for autos |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/aluminum-aleris/aleris-may-expand-capacity-in-europe-for-aluminum-sheet-for-autos-idUSL2N0WJ0U720150317 |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |publisher=Reuters |date=March 17, 2015}}</ref> Aleris' new aluminum body sheet facility in [[Lewisport, Kentucky]] opened in 2017.<ref name=\"Irwin\">{{cite news |last1=Irwin |first1=Jim |title=Aleris Launches Kentucky Aluminum Body Sheet Plant |url=http://www.wardsauto.com/technology/aleris-launches-kentucky-aluminum-body-sheet-plant |work=Ward's Auto |publisher=[[Ward's]] |date=November 22, 2017 |accessdate=June 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[China Zhongwang]] subsidiary Zhongwang USA and Aleris entered into a merger agreement in August 2016, marking the highest offer made by a Chinese firm for an American metal producing company.<ref name=\"Miller\">{{cite news |first1=John W. |last1=Miller |first2=Scott |last2=Patterson |title=Zhongwang's U.S. Business to Buy Aluminum Company Aleris |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-zhongwang-to-buy-aluminum-company-aleris-1472475642 |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=August 29, 2016 |issn=0099-9660 |oclc=781541372}}</ref> However, the $2.3 billion ($1.1 billion in cash plus $1.2 billion in debt)<ref name=Pooley/> agreement was abandoned in November 2017 because of uncertainties around regulations and approval by the [[Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Flannery |first1=Russell |title=China Billionaire, Aleris Abandon Merger Plan, Citing U.S. Regulatory Uncertainty |journal=[[Forbes]] |date=November 13, 2017 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2017/11/13/china-billionaire-aleris-abandon-merger-plan-citing-u-s-regulatory-uncertainty/#559ab1d85d5f |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |issn=0015-6914}}</ref><ref name=\"CD\">{{cite news |title=Zhongwang USA announces termination of proposed $2.3 billion acquisition of Aleris Corp |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2017-11/13/content_34494304.htm |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[China Daily]] |date=November 13, 2017 |first1=Wu |last1=Yong |author2=ZhengXin}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ng |first1=Eric |title=Aluminium giant China Zhongwang frustrated by US delays calls off Aleris acquisition |url=http://www.scmp.com/business/companies/article/2119889/aluminium-giant-china-zhongwang-frustrated-us-delays-calls-aleris |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |publisher=[[Alibaba Group]] |date=November 14, 2017}}</ref> [[Hindalco Industries]] was working on a $2.5 billion bid to acquire Aleris, as of October 2017,<ref name=Barman/> and [[Vedanta Resources]] was considering a bid, as of January 2018.<ref name=\"Chaki\">{{cite news |last1=Chaki |first1=Deborshi |title=Hindalco's Aleris acquisition bid may face competition from Vedanta |url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/AIyEw5hz6nyp4A4N9PORIJ/Hindalcos-Aleris-acquisition-bid-may-face-competition-from.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |publisher=[[HT Media]] |date=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 and 2018, Aleris entered into multi-year agreements to supply aluminum to [[Bombardier Inc.]] and [[Boeing]], respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Aleris expands supply agreement with Bombardier |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20171031/news/140601/aleris-expands-supply-agreement-bombardier |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |date=October 31, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Brief-Aleris Announces Contract with Boeing to Supply Aluminum |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/brief-aleris-announces-contract-with-boe/brief-aleris-announces-contract-with-boeing-to-supply-aluminum-idUSASC09ZHB |publisher=Reuters |date=May 3, 2018}}</ref> Aleris is ranked number 690 on the 2019 [[Fortune 1000]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Aleris |journal=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] |url=http://fortune.com/fortune500/aleris |accessdate=May 29, 2019 |issn=0015-8259}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Aleris was recognized with the accredited supplier award for outstanding quality performance by [[Airbus]] for the second consecutive year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.airbus.com/newsroom/news/en/2018/10/airbus-honours-its-top-performing-suppliers.html|title=Airbus honours its top-performing suppliers|website=Airbus|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Metals ==\nAleris developed a number of different alloys, such as [[7022 aluminium alloy|AA7022-T651]], a member of the [[Aluminium alloy#7000 series|7000 series of alloys]], which contains in addition to aluminum, [[silicon]], [[iron]], [[copper]], [[manganese]], [[magnesium]], [[chromium]], [[zinc]], [[titanium]] and [[zirconium]].<ref>{{Cite report|url=https://archive.org/details/DTIC_ADA516812|title=General Corrosion Resistance Comparisons of Medium- and High-Strength Aluminum Alloys for DOD Systems Using Laboratory-Based Accelerated Corrosion Methods|last=Placzankis|first=Brian E.|date=September 2009|publisher=U.S. Army Research Laboratory|issue=|doi=|volume=|pmid=|id=DTIC ADA516812; ARL-TR-4937|access-date=11 August 2018|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>  The company has also produced, in its [[Koblenz]] facility, [[5059 aluminium alloy|alloy AA5059-H131]].<ref>{{Cite report|url=https://archive.org/details/DTIC_ADA486670|title=Long-Term Accelerated Corrosion and Adhesion Assessment of CARC Prepared Aluminum Alloy 5059-H131 Using Three Different Surface Preparation Methods|last=Placzankis|first=Brian E.|last2=Hilgeman|first2=Amy L.|date=August 2008|publisher=Army Research Laboratory|issue=|doi=|volume=|pmid=|id=DTIC ADA486670; ARL-TR-457|access-date=August 12, 2018|via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref>{{Cite report|url=https://archive.org/stream/DTIC_ADA481408|title=Ballistic Performance Testing of Aluminum Alloy 5059-H131 and 5059-H136 for Armor Applications|last=Showalter|first=Dwight D.|last2=Placzankis|first2=Brian E.|date=May 2008|publisher=Army Research Laboratory|issue=|doi=|volume=|pmid=|id=DTIC ADA481408; ARL-TR-4427|last3=Burkins|first3=Matthew S.|access-date=August 12, 2018|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.aleris.com}}\n{{Bain Capital}}\n[[Category:2004 establishments in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Aluminium companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Apollo Global Management companies]]\n[[Category:Bain Capital companies]]<!-- via Sankaty Advisors -->\n[[Category:Beachwood, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Companies that filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in 2009]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies based in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Oaktree Capital Management]]\n[[Category:TPG Capital companies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Aleris Corporation\n| logo                = Aleris Logo.svg\n| logo_size           = \n| logo_alt            = \n| logo_caption        = The company's logo\n| logo_padding        = \n| image               = Aleris corporate HQ 02 - Beachwood Ohio (29218109022).jpg\n| image_size          = \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       = The company's headquarters in [[Beachwood, Ohio]], in 2016\n| trading_name        = \n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{Lang|[code]|[name]}}. -->\n| romanized_name      = \n| former_name         = \n| type                = [[Subsidiary company|Subsidiary]]\n| traded_as           = \n| ISIN                = \n| ISIN2               = \n| industry            = [[Manufacturing]]\n| genre               = \n| fate                = \n| predecessor         = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor           = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded             = {{Start date and age|2004}}\n| founder             = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct             = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location         = \n| hq_location_city    = [[Beachwood, Ohio]]\n| hq_location_country = United States\n| num_locations       = \n| num_locations_year  = <!-- Year of num_locations data (if known) -->\n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = Sean Stack ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]])\n| products            = [[Aluminium|Aluminum]]\n| brands              = \n| production          = \n| production_year     = <!-- Year of production data (if known) -->\n| services            = \n| revenue             = \n| revenue_year        = <!-- Year of revenue data (if known) -->\n| operating_income    = \n| income_year         = <!-- Year of operating_income data (if known) -->\n| net_income          = <!-- or: | profit = -->\n| net_income_year     = <!-- or: | profit_year = --><!-- Year of net_income/profit data (if known) -->\n| aum                 = <!-- Only for financial-service companies -->\n| assets              = \n| assets_year         = <!-- Year of assets data (if known) -->\n| equity              = \n| equity_year         = <!-- Year of equity data (if known) -->\n| owner               = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| members             = \n| members_year        = <!-- Year of members data (if known) -->\n| num_employees       = 5,000\n| num_employees_year  = 2015\n| parent              = [[Hindalco Industries]]\n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = \n| module              = <!-- Used to embed other templates -->\n| ratio               = <!-- Basel III ratio, for BANKS ONLY -->\n| rating              = <!-- credit rating, for BANKS ONLY -->\n| website             = {{URL|aleris.com}}\n| footnotes           = \n}}\n'''Aleris Corporation''' (also '''Aleris Inc.''' or '''Aleris International Inc.''') is an [[Aluminium|aluminum]] rolled products [[Production (economics)|producer]], based in [[Beachwood, Ohio]]. The company had approximately 5,000 employees globally as of mid 2015.\n\nOn 15 April 2020, Aleris Corporation was acquired by [[Hindalco Industries]] subsidiary Novelis Inc. for $2.8 billion. With the deal closure, Hindalco is now one of the world\u2019s largest aluminium makers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/hindalco-closes-2-8-billion-acquisition-of-us-based-aleris-corp-11586876784438.html|title=Hindalco closes $2.8-billion acquisition of US-based Aleris Corp|last=Thomas|first=Tanya|date=2020-04-14|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Corporate affairs==\nAleris is an [[Aluminium|aluminum]] rolled products [[Production (economics)|producer]], based in [[Beachwood, Ohio]], a suburb of [[Cleveland]].<ref name=\"Suttell\">{{cite news |last1=Suttell |first1=Scott |title=Aleris Inc. names new CEO |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20150713/NEWS/150719954/aleris-inc-names-new-ceo |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |publisher=[[Crain Communications]] |date=July 13, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Barman\">{{cite news |first1=Arijit |last1=Barman |first2=Vatsala |last2=Gaur |title=Hindalco weighing bid to acquire Aleris Corp of US |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/company/deals/hindalco-weighing-bid-to-acquire-aleris-corp-of-us/articleshow/61094708.cms |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Economic Times]] |publisher=[[The Times Group]] |date=October 16, 2017 |oclc=61311680}}</ref> The [[privately held company]] had approximately 5,000 employees overall, as of mid 2015, around 200 of which are based in [[Northeast Ohio]], including a manufacturing facility in [[Uhrichsville, Ohio]].<ref name=\"Suttell\"/><ref name=\"Pledger\">{{cite news |last1=Pledger |first1=Marcia |title=Reinvention: How Beachwood-based Aleris went from bankruptcy to expanding worldwide |url=https://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2015/02/reinvention_how_beachwood-base.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Plain Dealer]] |publisher=[[Advance Publications]] |date=February 9, 2015}}</ref> Aleris has [[private equity]] owners, including [[Apollo Global]] and [[Oaktree Capital Management]].<ref name=\"Suttell\"/><ref name=\"Pooley\">{{cite news |last1=Pooley |first1=Cat Rutter |title=Chinese aluminium entrepreneur abandons $2.3bn attempt to buy Aleris |url=https://www.ft.com/content/9138d8d2-aeee-3f98-a77b-052aa4fd2bc7 |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |date=November 13, 2017 |issn=0307-1766}}</ref>\n\nSteve Demetriou served as the first [[chairman]] and [[chief executive officer]] (CEO).<ref name=\"Suttell\"/><ref name=Pledger/> Sean Stack became CEO and joined the [[board of directors]] in mid 2015. Scott Graves became a non-executive chairman of Aleris' board at the same time.<ref name=\"Suttell\"/>\n\n==History==\nAleris was established in 2004,<ref name=\"Suttell\"/> the result of a merger between an [[Aluminium recycling|aluminum recycling]] company and an aluminum rolled products company.<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris operated as a [[portfolio company]] of [[Texas Pacific Group]],<ref name=\"Wabash\">{{cite news |title=Aleris to buy aluminum producer |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20070705/FREE/70705001/aleris-to-buy-aluminum-producer |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |date=July 5, 2007}}</ref> and expanded via acquisitions during its early history. The company acquired [[Corus Group]]'s aluminum [[extrusion]] and rolling businesses for approximately $894 million (\u20ac700 million) in 2006,<ref name=\"Buys\">{{cite news |title=Aleris Buys Aluminium Assets from Corus |url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2006/05/24/aleris-buys-aluminium-assets-from-corus/ |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |date=May 24, 2006 |issn=0362-4331 |oclc=1645522}}</ref> and Wabash Alloys for an undisclosed amount in 2007.<ref name=Wabash/> Following the Corus acquisition, Aleris had approximately 8,800 employees and more than 40 manufacturing facilities globally.<ref name=Buys/> \n\nIn February 2009, the [[United States Department of Justice|Department of Justice]] filed suit against the company, alleging that 15 of its plants had violated the [[Clean Air Act (United States)|Clean Air Act]] by emission of pollutants. Aleris settled the suit with the government in August 2009, and agreed to pay a $4.6 million fine and spend an additional $4.2 million on new pollution controls at its plants.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2009/08/aluminum_recycler_aleris_inter.html | title=Aluminum recycler Aleris International Inc. to pay $4.6 million EPA fine | first=Frank | last=Bentayou | date=August 5, 2009 | work=[[The Plain Dealer]] | location=Cleveland, Ohio | accessdate=June 26, 2018}}</ref> The [[financial crisis of 2007\u20132008]] and [[Great Recession]] caused significant downturns in production, and Aleris experienced a 40 percent volume decline during 2008\u20132009.<ref name=Pledger/> In 2009, the company filed for [[Chapter 11, Title 11, United States Code|Chapter 11]] bankruptcy,<ref name=\"Pledger\"/> and Apollo, Oaktree Capital, and [[Sankaty Advisors]] became owners in 2010.<ref name=Pooley/><ref name=\"Reorganization\">{{cite news |title=Update 1-Aleris reorganization plan confirmed by court |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/aleris/update-1-aleris-reorganization-plan-confirmed-by-court-idUSSGE64C0KT20100513 |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |publisher=Reuters |date=May 13, 2010}}</ref> Aleris stabilized its financial position and significantly reduced debt. The company also invested in its facilities, building a new aerospace plate mill in China during the early 2010s, finishing a $70 million expansion of its facility in [[Duffel]] (2013),<ref name=\"Opens\">{{cite news |last1=Schoenberger |first1=Robert |title=Aleris International opens new aluminum mill in Belgium |url=https://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2013/03/aleris_international_opens_new.html |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |date=March 15, 2013 |work=The Plain Dealer}}</ref> and improving its plant in [[Ashville, Ohio]], in 2014.<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris acquired Nichols Aluminum and its production facilities in [[Davenport, Iowa]], [[Decatur, Alabama]], and [[Lincolnshire, Illinois]], for $110 million cash in 2014.<ref name=\"Berry\">{{cite news |last1=Berry |first1=Lucy |title=Aleris purchases Nichols Aluminum, which operates Decatur plant, for $110 million cash |url=https://www.al.com/business/index.ssf/2014/04/aleris_purchases_nichols_alumi.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Birmingham News]] |publisher=Advance Publications |date=April 1, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"DeWitt\">{{cite news |last1=DeWitt |first1=Jennifer |title=Aleris to aquire Nichols Aluminum from Quanex |url=https://qctimes.com/business/aleris-to-aquire-nichols-aluminum-from-quanex/article_15749d1c-06de-5f67-8b34-b98767c8b1c6.html |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |work=[[Quad-City Times]] |publisher=Lee Enterprises |date=February 10, 2014}}</ref> The aluminum finishing plant in Decatur was closed before the end of the year to streamline operations. Aleris had more than 40 production facilities in North America, Europe, and Asia, as of October 2014.<ref name=\"Closure\">{{cite news |last1=Berry |first1=Lucy |title=Aleris International announces Nichols Aluminum plant closure, 95 job cuts in Decatur |url=https://www.al.com/business/index.ssf/2014/10/aleris_international_announces.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Birmingham News]] |publisher=Advance Publications |date=October 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, the company focused on selling its extrusion and recycling businesses, and planned to raise approximately $600 million in capital. The divestitures decreased the number of employees to around 5,000.<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris abandoned plans to complete an [[initial public offering]] in 2015.<ref name=Pooley/><ref>{{cite news |title=Update 1-Private equity-backed aluminum processor Aleris scraps IPO plan |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/aleris-ipo/update-1-private-equity-backed-aluminum-processor-aleris-scraps-ipo-plan-idUSL4N0VF79320150205 |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |publisher=Reuters |date=February 5, 2015}}</ref> The company had approximately 7,000 employees in the U.S., Europe, and China at the time, including approximately 340 in Uhrichsville and 250 in [[Greater Cleveland]].<ref name=Pledger/> Aleris was also among the largest aluminum [[Sheet metal|sheet]] suppliers for [[semi-trailer]]s, and the leading aluminum sheet supplier for the U.S. residential construction industry.<ref name=Pledger/> The company increased production as the [[automotive industry]] began using more aluminum than steel.<ref name=Pledger/><ref name=\"Expand\">{{cite news |last1=Cohen |first1=Luc |title=Aleris may expand capacity in Europe for aluminum sheet for autos |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/aluminum-aleris/aleris-may-expand-capacity-in-europe-for-aluminum-sheet-for-autos-idUSL2N0WJ0U720150317 |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |publisher=Reuters |date=March 17, 2015}}</ref> Aleris' new aluminum body sheet facility in [[Lewisport, Kentucky]] opened in 2017.<ref name=\"Irwin\">{{cite news |last1=Irwin |first1=Jim |title=Aleris Launches Kentucky Aluminum Body Sheet Plant |url=http://www.wardsauto.com/technology/aleris-launches-kentucky-aluminum-body-sheet-plant |work=Ward's Auto |publisher=[[Ward's]] |date=November 22, 2017 |accessdate=June 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[China Zhongwang]] subsidiary Zhongwang USA and Aleris entered into a merger agreement in August 2016, marking the highest offer made by a Chinese firm for an American metal producing company.<ref name=\"Miller\">{{cite news |first1=John W. |last1=Miller |first2=Scott |last2=Patterson |title=Zhongwang's U.S. Business to Buy Aluminum Company Aleris |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-zhongwang-to-buy-aluminum-company-aleris-1472475642 |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=August 29, 2016 |issn=0099-9660 |oclc=781541372}}</ref> However, the $2.3 billion ($1.1 billion in cash plus $1.2 billion in debt)<ref name=Pooley/> agreement was abandoned in November 2017 because of uncertainties around regulations and approval by the [[Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Flannery |first1=Russell |title=China Billionaire, Aleris Abandon Merger Plan, Citing U.S. Regulatory Uncertainty |journal=[[Forbes]] |date=November 13, 2017 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2017/11/13/china-billionaire-aleris-abandon-merger-plan-citing-u-s-regulatory-uncertainty/#559ab1d85d5f |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |issn=0015-6914}}</ref><ref name=\"CD\">{{cite news |title=Zhongwang USA announces termination of proposed $2.3 billion acquisition of Aleris Corp |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2017-11/13/content_34494304.htm |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[China Daily]] |date=November 13, 2017 |first1=Wu |last1=Yong |author2=ZhengXin}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ng |first1=Eric |title=Aluminium giant China Zhongwang frustrated by US delays calls off Aleris acquisition |url=http://www.scmp.com/business/companies/article/2119889/aluminium-giant-china-zhongwang-frustrated-us-delays-calls-aleris |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |publisher=[[Alibaba Group]] |date=November 14, 2017}}</ref> [[Hindalco Industries]] was working on a $2.5 billion bid to acquire Aleris, as of October 2017,<ref name=Barman/> and [[Vedanta Resources]] was considering a bid, as of January 2018.<ref name=\"Chaki\">{{cite news |last1=Chaki |first1=Deborshi |title=Hindalco's Aleris acquisition bid may face competition from Vedanta |url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/AIyEw5hz6nyp4A4N9PORIJ/Hindalcos-Aleris-acquisition-bid-may-face-competition-from.html |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |publisher=[[HT Media]] |date=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 and 2018, Aleris entered into multi-year agreements to supply aluminum to [[Bombardier Inc.]] and [[Boeing]], respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Aleris expands supply agreement with Bombardier |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20171031/news/140601/aleris-expands-supply-agreement-bombardier |accessdate=June 26, 2018 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |date=October 31, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Brief-Aleris Announces Contract with Boeing to Supply Aluminum |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/brief-aleris-announces-contract-with-boe/brief-aleris-announces-contract-with-boeing-to-supply-aluminum-idUSASC09ZHB |publisher=Reuters |date=May 3, 2018}}</ref> Aleris is ranked number 690 on the 2019 [[Fortune 1000]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Aleris |journal=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] |url=http://fortune.com/fortune500/aleris |accessdate=May 29, 2019 |issn=0015-8259}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Aleris was recognized with the accredited supplier award for outstanding quality performance by [[Airbus]] for the second consecutive year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.airbus.com/newsroom/news/en/2018/10/airbus-honours-its-top-performing-suppliers.html|title=Airbus honours its top-performing suppliers|website=Airbus|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Metals ==\nAleris developed a number of different alloys, such as [[7022 aluminium alloy|AA7022-T651]], a member of the [[Aluminium alloy#7000 series|7000 series of alloys]], which contains in addition to aluminum, [[silicon]], [[iron]], [[copper]], [[manganese]], [[magnesium]], [[chromium]], [[zinc]], [[titanium]] and [[zirconium]].<ref>{{Cite report|url=https://archive.org/details/DTIC_ADA516812|title=General Corrosion Resistance Comparisons of Medium- and High-Strength Aluminum Alloys for DOD Systems Using Laboratory-Based Accelerated Corrosion Methods|last=Placzankis|first=Brian E.|date=September 2009|publisher=U.S. Army Research Laboratory|issue=|doi=|volume=|pmid=|id=DTIC ADA516812; ARL-TR-4937|access-date=11 August 2018|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>  The company has also produced, in its [[Koblenz]] facility, [[5059 aluminium alloy|alloy AA5059-H131]].<ref>{{Cite report|url=https://archive.org/details/DTIC_ADA486670|title=Long-Term Accelerated Corrosion and Adhesion Assessment of CARC Prepared Aluminum Alloy 5059-H131 Using Three Different Surface Preparation Methods|last=Placzankis|first=Brian E.|last2=Hilgeman|first2=Amy L.|date=August 2008|publisher=Army Research Laboratory|issue=|doi=|volume=|pmid=|id=DTIC ADA486670; ARL-TR-457|access-date=August 12, 2018|via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref>{{Cite report|url=https://archive.org/stream/DTIC_ADA481408|title=Ballistic Performance Testing of Aluminum Alloy 5059-H131 and 5059-H136 for Armor Applications|last=Showalter|first=Dwight D.|last2=Placzankis|first2=Brian E.|date=May 2008|publisher=Army Research Laboratory|issue=|doi=|volume=|pmid=|id=DTIC ADA481408; ARL-TR-4427|last3=Burkins|first3=Matthew S.|access-date=August 12, 2018|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.aleris.com}}\n{{Bain Capital}}\n[[Category:2004 establishments in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Aluminium companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Apollo Global Management companies]]\n[[Category:Bain Capital companies]]<!-- via Sankaty Advisors -->\n[[Category:Beachwood, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Companies that filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in 2009]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies based in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Oaktree Capital Management]]\n[[Category:TPG Capital companies]]\n", "name_user": "JayminShahOfficial", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aleris"}
{"title_page": "Andr\u00e9s Guardado", "text_new": "{{spanish name|Guardado|Hern\u00e1ndez}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Andr\u00e9s Guardado\n| image = Mex-Kor (25) (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Guardado with [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]]\n| fullname = Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s Guardado Hern\u00e1ndez<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fifadata.com/document/FWC/2014/pdf/FWC_2014_SquadLists.pdf|title=2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil: List of players|publisher=FIFA|page=25|format=PDF|accessdate=14 July 2014}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|9|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Guadalajara]], Mexico\n| height = 1.69 m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realbetisbalompie.es/primer-equipo/jugador/a-guardado-23581|title=Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s Guardado Hern\u00e1ndez|publisher=Real Betis|language=Spanish|accessdate=3 February 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]] / [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]] / [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left-back]]\n| currentclub = [[Real Betis|Betis]]\n| clubnumber = 18\n| youthyears1 = 1993\u20132005 | youthclubs1 = [[Club Atlas|Atlas]]\n| years1 = 2005\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[Club Atlas|Atlas]] | caps1 = 64 | goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2007\u20132012 | clubs2 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] | caps2 = 137 | goals2 = 23\n| years3 = 2012\u20132015| clubs3 = [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] | caps3 = 48 | goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2014 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] (loan) | caps4 = 4 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] (loan) | caps5 = 22 | goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2015\u20132017 | clubs6 = [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] | caps6 = 58 | goals6 = 3\n| years7 = 2017\u2013 | clubs7 = [[Real Betis|Betis]] | caps7 = 80 | goals7 = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2005\u2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] | nationalcaps1 = 158 | nationalgoals1 = 28\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 7 July 2019\n| medaltemplates = \n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|MEX}}}}\n{{Medal|W|[[CONCACAF Gold Cup]]|[[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2011]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[CONCACAF Gold Cup]]|[[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2015]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[CONCACAF Gold Cup]]|[[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2019]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[CONCACAF Gold Cup]]|[[2007 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2007]]}}\n{{Medal|3rd|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]|[[2007 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2007 Venezuela]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s Guardado Hern\u00e1ndez''' ({{IPA-es|an\u02c8d\u027eez \u0263wa\u027e\u02c8\u00f0a\u00f0o}}; born 28 September 1986) is a Mexican professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Spanish club [[Real Betis]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]]. Mainly a [[midfielder]], he can also operate as a [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]] or [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]].\n\nPopularly known as ''Principito'' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for ''[[The Little Prince|Little Prince]]''),<ref name=TEN>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/es/news/4194/editoriales/2015/08/20/14607112/andr%C3%A9s-guardado-el-principito-cumple-10-a%C3%B1os|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, el Principito cumple 10 a\u00f1os|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, the Little Prince celebrates 10 years|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|first=Roberto|last=Navarro|language=Spanish|date=20 August 2015|accessdate=1 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.elmundo.es/deportes/2016/03/15/56e72076e2704ed7568b45c1.html|title=Guardado, 'el Principito' de Eindhoven|trans-title=Guardado, Eindhoven's 'Little Prince'|newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|first=Miguel|last=Ria\u00f1o|language=Spanish|date=15 March 2016|accessdate=1 May 2016}}</ref> he came through the youth ranks at [[Club Atlas|Atlas]], then signed with Spain's [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo]], where he spent five seasons. In 2012 he joined another team in the country, [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], with brief loan stints at [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] and [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], permanently joining the latter club in 2015 and winning two [[Eredivisie]] titles.\n\nA [[Mexico national football team|Mexican international]] since 2005, Guardado represented the country in four [[FIFA World Cup|World Cups]], four [[CONCACAF Gold Cup|Gold Cups]] \u2013 winning the [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2011]], [[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2015]] and [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2019]] tournaments \u2013 two [[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]s and two [[FIFA Confederations Cup|Confederations Cups]], winning over 150 [[Cap (sport)|caps]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://elpais.com/deportes/2018/01/15/tiempo_extra/1516038138_681908.html | title = Andr\u00e9s Guardado, el capit\u00e1n sin brazalete |trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, the captain without armband | newspaper = [[El Pa\u00eds]] | first = Diego | last = Mancera | language = Spanish | date = 15 January 2018 | accessdate = 4 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.90min.com/es/posts/6327261-los-jugadores-del-tri-con-mas-de-100-partidos-disputados|title=Los jugadores del Tri con m\u00e1s de 100 partidos disputados|trans-title=The ''Tri'' players with more than 100 matches played|publisher=90 Min|first=Elias|last=Manzur Carrera|language=Spanish|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=16 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Atlas===\nBorn in [[Guadalajara]], [[Jalisco]], Guardado started playing professionally for [[Club Atlas]], joining the team's youth system at the age of seven and going on to appear in two full [[Liga MX|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] seasons. He made his league debut on 20 August 2005, in a 3\u20132 home win against [[C.F. Pachuca]].<ref name=TEN/>\n\nIn the summer of 2006, press speculation linked Guardado to several [[Serie A]] teams<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/358440.html | title = Italia, tras Guardado |trans-title=Italy, following Guardado | newspaper = [[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]] | first = \u00c1ngel | last = Parra | language = Spanish | date = 29 June 2006 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> as well as [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.esmas.com/deportes/futbol/557591.html | title = Interesa Andr\u00e9s Guardado al Real Madrid | trans-title = Andr\u00e9s Guardado interests Real Madrid | publisher = Es M\u00e1s | language = Spanish | date = 10 August 2006 | accessdate = 16 February 2014 | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100104150657/http://www.esmas.com/deportes/futbol/557591.html | archive-date = 4 January 2010 | df = dmy-all}}</ref> but [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]] moved quickly and made an offer of [[Euro|\u20ac]]7 million for 75% of his rights. Atlas accepted the offer and the transfer was finalized on 7 July 2007, making him the most expensive ever Mexican player. Atlas retained a 25% sell-on-fee as long as it held the remaining 25% of his rights.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.jornada.unam.mx/2007/07/11/index.php?section=deportes&article=a17n1dep | title = Andres Guardado se va al Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a de Espa\u00f1a |trans-title=Andres Guardado goes to Spain's Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a | publisher = La Jornada | language = Spanish | date = 10 July 2007 | accessdate = 9 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Deportivo===\n[[File:Andr\u00e9s Guardado.jpg|thumb|125px|Guardado in action for Deportivo in 2008]]\nGuardado was officially introduced on 24 July 2007, with the Spanish team giving him the number 18 shirt. He made his [[La Liga]] debut on 26 August in a 0\u20133 home loss against [[UD Almer\u00eda]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/226430?cc=5739 | title = Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a 0\u20133 Almeria | publisher = [[ESPN FC]] | date = 26 August 2007 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> and finished [[2007\u201308 La Liga|his first season]] with 26 games and five goals as ''Depor'' finished in ninth position, eventually [[2008 UEFA Intertoto Cup|qualifying]] to the [[UEFA Intertoto Cup]]&nbsp;\u2013 and [[2008\u201309 UEFA Cup|the subsequent]] [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]], where he scored in a 3\u20130 group stage home win over [[Feyenoord]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/114/mexico/2008/12/01/990531/mexicans-abroad-guardado-on-a-hot-streak | title = Mexicans abroad: Guardado on a hot streak | publisher = Goal | first = C\u00e9sar | last = Garc\u00eda | date = 1 December 2008 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nCoach [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Lotina]] stated that Guardado was a key player for Deportivo, and admired his talent and character.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mediotiempo.com/noticia.php?id_noticia=42265 | title = Guardado a reference player in Deportivo | publisher = Medio Tiempo | date = 24 July 2007 | accessdate = 16 February 2014 | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070930031338/http://www.mediotiempo.com/noticia.php?id_noticia=42265 | archive-date = 30 September 2007 | df = dmy-all}}</ref> He solidified himself as first-choice for the team, providing several [[Assist (football)|assists]] and being charged with [[Set piece (football)|set pieces]]; he was also hampered by several injuries, however.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/114/mexico/2010/04/19/1885741/mexicans-abroad-guardados-injured | title = Mexicans abroad: Guardado's injured | publisher = Goal | first = Andrea | last = Mart\u00ednez | date = 19 April 2010 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.marca.com/2010/12/23/futbol/equipos/deportivo/1293088197.html | title = Guardado viaja a M\u00e9xico para recuperarse de su lesi\u00f3n |trans-title=Guardado travels to Mexico to recover from injury | newspaper = [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] | location = Madrid | language = Spanish | date = 23 December 2010 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nGuardado only managed to appear in 20 matches in [[2010\u201311 La Liga|2010\u201311]], and the [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicians]] were relegated to [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] after 20 years. On 27 March 2012 he confirmed that [[2011\u201312 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2011\u201312]] would be his last season with the club,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.goal.com/es/news/21/fichajes/2012/03/27/2996090/jos%C3%A9-andr%C3%A9s-guardado-confirma-que-se-marcha-de-la-coru%C3%B1a | title = Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s Guardado confirma que se marcha de La Coru\u00f1a |trans-title=Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s Guardado confirms he is leaving La Coru\u00f1a | publisher = Goal | first = Felipe | last = Del Valle Iturriaga | language = Spanish | date = 27 March 2012 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> and he scored a career-best 11 goals as his team returned to the top level as champions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vavel.com/es/futbol/2016/07/05/deportivo-de-la-coruna/666277-9-anos-del-fichaje-de-andres-guardado.html|title=D\u00e9por: nueve a\u00f1os del fichaje de Andr\u00e9s Guardado|trans-title=D\u00e9por: nine years of Andr\u00e9s Guardado's signing|publisher=[[Vavel]]|first=Jos\u00e9|last=Souto Lousada|language=Spanish|date=5 July 2016|accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> Halfway through the season, he was voted by their fans as best player,<ref name=\"Best\">{{cite news|url=https://www.informador.mx/Deportes/Es-Guardado-el-mejor-del-Depor-para-la-aficion-20120102-0073.html|title=Es Guardado el mejor del Depor para la afici\u00f3n|trans-title=Guardado is the best of Depor according to fans|newspaper=[[El Informador (Mexico)|El Informador]]|language=Spanish|date=2 January 2012|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref> and was also named the competition's best attacking midfielder;<ref name=\"ATTM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com.mx/news/73083-andres-guardado-fue-el-mejor-medio-ofensivo-de-segunda-division|title=Guardado, el mejor medio ofensivo de Segunda|trans-title=Guardado, best attacking midfielder of ''Segunda''|publisher=[[Fox Sports]]|language=Spanish|date=13 November 2012|accessdate=26 December 2019}}</ref> additionally, he eventually surpassed [[Juan Carlos Valer\u00f3n]] as the highest provider of assists.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/2012/04/17/futbol/futbol_internacional/mexico/1334673823.html|title=Guardado, nueve goles y nueve asistencias|trans-title=Guardado, nine goals and nine assists|newspaper=Marca|language=Spanish|date=17 April 2012|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Valencia===\n[[File:Guardado Val\u00e8ncia.jpg|left|thumb|125px|Guardado taking a shot for [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in 2012]]\nOn 28 May 2012, Guardado signed a four-year contract with [[Valencia CF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenciacf.com/contenidos/Actualidad/Noticias/2012/05/Noticia_37492.html?__locale=es|title=Comunicado oficial|trans-title=Official announcement|publisher=Valencia CF|language=Spanish|date=28 May 2012|accessdate=28 May 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120530182011/http://www.valenciacf.com/contenidos/Actualidad/Noticias/2012/05/Noticia_37492.html?__locale=es|archivedate=30 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballcracy.com/transfers-2/valencia-sign-andres-guardado-from-deportivo|title=Valencia sign Andres Guardado from Deportivo|publisher=Footballcracy|date=29 May 2012|accessdate=29 May 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120530221614/http://www.footballcracy.com/transfers-2/valencia-sign-andres-guardado-from-deportivo/|archivedate=30 May 2012}}</ref> He made his debut on 19 August, playing 66 minutes in a 1\u20131 away draw against Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://espnfc.com/gamecast?id=348504&cc=5739 | title = Real held by Valencia in season opener | publisher = ESPN FC | date = 19 August 2012 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> His maiden appearance in the [[UEFA Champions League]] took place on 12 September, in a [[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League|1\u20132 group stage loss]] at eventual winners [[FC Bayern Munich]];<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.informador.mx/Deportes/Amargo-debut-para-Andres-Guardado-20120920-0202.html|title=Amargo debut para Andr\u00e9s Guardado|trans-title=Sour debut for Andr\u00e9s Guardado|newspaper=El Informador|language=Spanish|date=12 September 2012|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> during [[2012\u201313 La Liga|his first season]] he featured regularly at [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]], mainly due to the serious injury of [[J\u00e9r\u00e9my Mathieu]].<ref name=\"Lecture\">{{cite news|url=http://www.superdeporte.es/valencia/2013/01/02/valverde-instruye-lateral-guardado/183793.html|title=Valverde instruye al lateral Guardado|trans-title=Valverde lectures left back Guardado|newspaper=[[Super Deporte]]|first=Pau|last=Fuster|language=Spanish|date=2 January 2013|accessdate=16 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolpasion.mx/index.php?seccion=noticias&idn=8656|title=Guardado, el lateral perfecto|trans-title=Guardado, the perfect full back|publisher=F\u00fatbol Pasi\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=14 January 2013|accessdate=16 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nGuardado scored his first goal for the ''Che'' on 12 May 2013, contributing to a 4\u20130 rout at [[Rayo Vallecano]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2012_13/primera/jornada_35/ray_val/|title=Paseo matinal en Vallecas|trans-title=Morning walk in Vallecas|newspaper=Marca|location=Madrid|first=Santiago|last=Siguero|language=Spanish|date=12 May 2013|accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref> and he featured mostly in the backline in the following months. On 30 January 2014, [[Bundesliga]] club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] announced that they had signed him on loan for the rest of the season, with an option to buy afterwards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000284711.php|title=Leverkusen take Guardado on loan|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|date=30 January 2014|accessdate=31 January 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131090740/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000284711.php|archivedate=31 January 2014}}</ref> He made his debut on 2 February in a [[2013\u201314 DFB-Pokal|0\u20131 loss]] against [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]] for the [[DFB-Pokal]], playing as a left wingback.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starmedia.com/deportes/futbol/liga-alemana/derrota-bayer-leverkusen-en-debut-mexicano-andres-guardado.html|title=Derrota del Bayer Leverkusen en debut del mexicano Andr\u00e9s Guardado|trans-title=Defeat for Bayer Leverkusen in Mexican Andr\u00e9s Guardado's debut|publisher=[[Starmedia]]|first=Hansel|last=Tobar|language=Spanish|date=2 February 2014|accessdate=9 June 2014|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140609071457/http://www.starmedia.com/deportes/futbol/liga-alemana/derrota-bayer-leverkusen-en-debut-mexicano-andres-guardado.html|archive-date=9 June 2014}}</ref> \n\nGuardado's playing time at both the [[Mestalla Stadium]] and the [[BayArena]] was hampered by injuries and loss of form.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/114/mexico/2014/08/27/5062826/tom-marshall-andres-guardado-perseveres-in-euro-adventure|title=Tom Marshall: Andres Guardado perseveres in Euro adventure|publisher=Goal|first=Tom|last=Marshall|date=27 August 2014|accessdate=9 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Spot\">{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerpro.com/thecentercircle/on-the-spot-andres-guardado/|title=On the spot: Andr\u00e9s Guardado|publisher=Soccer Pro|first=Collin|last=Carpio|date=15 June 2016|accessdate=16 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxdeportes.com/liga-mx/story/diez-veces-andres-guardado/|title=Diez veces Andr\u00e9s Guardado|trans-title=Ten times Andr\u00e9s Guardado|publisher=[[Fox Deportes]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===PSV Eindhoven===\n[[File:Zenit-PSV (1).jpg|thumb|Guardado with PSV in 2015]]\nFor [[2014\u201315 Eredivisie|2014\u201315]], still owned by Valencia, Guardado joined [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psv.nl/Nieuws/Nieuwspagina/PSV-huurt-Mexicaan-Andres-Guardado.htm|title=PSV huurt Mexicaan Andr\u00e9s Guardado|trans-title=PSV get loan of Mexican Andr\u00e9s Guardado|publisher=PSV Eindhoven|language=Dutch|date=26 August 2014|accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref> He made his [[Eredivisie]] debut on 31 August 2014 against [[Vitesse Arnhem]] at [[Philips Stadion]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://archivo.eluniversal.com.mx/deportes/2014/psv-gana-2-0-al-vitesse-guardado-debuta-1034450.html|title=PSV gana 2\u20130 al Vitesse en debut de Guardado|trans-title=PSV defeat Vitesse 2\u20130 on debut of Guardado|newspaper=El Universal|language=Spanish|date=31 August 2014|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref> He managed to wear the [[Captain (association football)|captain]]'s armband within his first months,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.livesoccertv.com/es/news/13718/psv-agrees-terms-with-valencia-to-sign-midfielder-andres-guardado-for-good|title=PSV agrees terms with Valencia to sign midfielder Andres Guardado for good|publisher=Live Soccer TV|date=2015|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref> won the Player of the Month award for November,<ref name=\"November\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1433/PSV/article/detail/3802878/2014/12/03/Guardado-Zelfs-op-kunstgras-goed-cijfer-Mooi.dhtml|title=Guardado: Zelfs op kunstgras goed cijfer? Mooi!|trans-title=Guardado: Good grades even on artificial turf? Nice!|newspaper=[[Algemeen Dagblad]]|first=Maarten|last=Wijffels|language=Dutch|date=3 December 2014|accessdate=9 February 2015}}</ref> and on 7 March of the following year he scored his first goal for his new club, contributing to a 3\u20130 away victory over [[Go Ahead Eagles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psv.nl/psv/nieuws/artikel/psv-veel-te-sterk-voor-go-ahead-03.htm|title=PSV veel te sterk voor Go Ahead: 0\u20133|trans-title=PSV too strong for Go Ahead: 0\u20133|publisher=PSV Eindhoven|language=Dutch|date=7 March 2015|accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March 2015, prior to the match against [[FC Groningen]] and amidst rumours of a transfer to [[AFC Ajax]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/es-mx/news/4783/mexicanos-por-el-mundo/2015/02/24/9243242/aconsejan-al-ajax-fichar-a-andr%C3%A9s-guardado|title=Aconsejan al Ajax fichar a Andr\u00e9s Guardado|trans-title=Ajax advised to sign Andr\u00e9s Guardado|publisher=Goal|language=Spanish|date=24 February 2015|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref> PSV fans displayed a Mexican flag [[tifo]] and a banner in Spanish which read \"Andr\u00e9s Guardado, our Golden Mexican Eagle. He has to stay in PSV Eindhoven. Our house is your house, Andr\u00e9s\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fansided.com/2015/03/15/psv-fans-pay-tribute-to-andres-guardado-before-match-video/|title=PSV fans pay tribute to Andres Guardado before match (Video)|publisher=Fansided|first=Josh|last=Sanchez|date=15 March 2015|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref> On 27 March, PSV announced that they had reached a deal with Valencia over a permanent transfer, for an undisclosed fee and three years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/psv-agree-terms-with-valencia-over-andres-guardado.htm|title=PSV agree terms with Valencia over Andr\u00e9s Guardado|publisher=PSV Eindhoven|date=27 March 2015|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref> \n\nOn 18 April 2015, with three matches to spare, the team [[2014\u201315 Eredivisie|won the league championship]] after a 4\u20131 win over [[SC Heerenveen]], with Guardado playing the full 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/psv-crowned-eredivisie-champions-after-a-41-win.htm|title=PSV crowned Eredivisie champions after a 4\u20131 win|publisher=PSV Eindhoven|date=18 April 2015|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref> At the end of his first season, his impressive performances led him to be named the player of the year by Dutch magazines ''[[Algemeen Dagblad]]''<ref name=\"AD\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/5610/Eredivisie/article/detail/4028645/2015/05/17/PSV-er-Guardado-beste-speler-Eredivisie-Markiet-de-slechtste.dhtml|title=PSV'er Guardado beste speler Eredivisie, Markiet de slechtste|trans-title=PSV's Guardado best player of the Eredivisie, Markiet the worst|newspaper=Algemeen Dagblad|language=Dutch|date=17 May 2015|accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref> and ''[[Voetbal International]]''.<ref name=\"VI\">{{cite news|url=http://www.vi.nl/speler-van-de-week/speler-van-het-jaar-guardado-bepaalt-wat-psv-doet.htm|title=Speler van het Jaar: Guardado bepaalt wat PSV doet|trans-title=Player of the Year: Guardado determines how PSV performs|publisher=[[Voetbal International]]|language=Dutch|date=18 May 2015|accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[2015\u201316 Eredivisie|The following campaign]], Guardado contributed with 25 appearances to help the side successfully defend their title,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espndeportes.espn.go.com/futbol/nota/_/id/2670423/dramatico-titulo-para-guardado-y-moreno-en-la-eredivisie|title=Dram\u00e1tico t\u00edtulo para Guardado y Moreno en la Eredivisie|trans-title=Dramatic title for Guardado and Moreno in the Eredivisie|publisher=[[ESPN Deportes]]|language=Spanish|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=4 June 2016}}</ref> finishing with nine assists as the team's second-highest provider.<ref name=\"Spot\"/> He was listed on Football Oranje's team of the season.<ref name=Oranje>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/eredivisie-team-season-2/|title=Football-Oranje\u2019s Eredivisie 2015/16 team of the season|publisher=Football Oranje|date=9 May 2016|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> \n\nOn 31 July 2016, Guardado was in the starting eleven against [[Feyenoord]], who were [[2016 Johan Cruyff Shield|defeated 1\u20130]] in the [[Johan Cruyff Shield]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futboltotal.com.mx/2016/07/psv-guardado-conquistan-la-supercopa/|title=PSV y Guardado conquistan la Supercopa|trans-title=PSV and Guardado win the Supercup|publisher=F\u00fatbol Total|language=Spanish|date=31 July 2016|accessdate=31 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Betis===\nDespite rumors linking him to a possible move to [[Atlanta United]] and [[Los Angeles FC]] of the [[Major League Soccer]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2017/07/07/andres-guardado-real-betis-psv-transfer-mls-mexico|title=Despite MLS rumors and links, Mexico's Andres Guardado leaves PSV for Real Betis|publisher=[[Sports Illustrated]]|date=7 July 2017|accessdate=8 July 2017}}</ref> it was announced on 27 July 2017 that Spanish club [[Real Betis]] had signed Guardado for a reported \u20ac2.3 million on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/guardado-leaves-psv-real-betis/|title=Guardado leaves PSV for Real Betis|publisher=Football Oranje|date=7 July 2017|accessdate=7 July 2017}}</ref> The following month he was named their co-captain,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/la-liga/andres-guardado-elegido-como-capitan-del-betis|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, elegido como capit\u00e1n del Betis|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, chosen as Betis captain|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=19 August 2017|accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref> and on 20 August he made his competitive debut, playing all 90 minutes in a 2\u20130 loss to [[FC Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://siete24.mx/deportes/duro-debut-de-guardado-ante-barcelona|title=Duro debut de Guardado ante Barcelona|trans-title=Hard debut for Guardado against Barcelona|publisher=Siete 24|language=Spanish|date=20 August 2017|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 25 November, in a 2\u20132 home draw against [[Girona FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/claro-mx/futbol/mexicanos-mundo/2017/11/25/5a19c634ca4741613d8b4649.html|title=Guardado marca su primer gol con el Betis|trans-title=Guardado scores his first goal with Betis|newspaper=Marca|language=Spanish|date=25 November 2017|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, the 33-year-old Guardado renewed his contract until 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://playingfor90.com/2019/12/04/andres-guardado-renews-real-betis/|title=Andres Guardado renews with Real Betis|publisher=Playing for 90|first=Ernesto|last=Hernandez|date=4 December 2019|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nGuardado made his first appearance for [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] in a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] on 14 December 2005, four months after his first-team debut with Atlas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/liga-mx/hungria-dulce-regalo-navidad-acabo-maleficio-europeos|title=Hungr\u00eda fue un dulce regalo de Navidad... Se acab\u00f3 el maleficio de europeos|trans-title=Hungary was a sweet Christmas present... European jinx ended|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=15 December 2005|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> He was then called up to represent his country at the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] in Germany,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/volpe-lista-oficial-jugadores-iran-alemania-2006|title=La Volpe da a conocer la lista oficial de los jugadores que ir\u00e1n a Alemania 2006|trans-title=La Volpe releases official list of players who will go to Germany 2006|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=3 April 2006|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> where he appeared in the round of 16 1\u20132 loss to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], starting as a shifting [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]]/[[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wing-back]] alongside [[Ram\u00f3n Morales]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://el9ymedio.com/2018/09/04/guardado-el-origen-del-centrocampista/|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, el origen del centrocampista|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, origins of the midfielder|publisher=El 9 y Medio|first=Ricardo|last=L\u00f3pez|language=Spanish|date=4 September 2018|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref> but was replaced by [[Gonzalo Pineda]] after picking up an injury in the second half;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2006/5103878.stm|title=Argentina 2\u20131 Mexico (aet)|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=24 June 2006|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/podolski-and-messi-set-berlin-battle-14005|title=Podolski and Messi set up Berlin battle|publisher=FIFA|date=24 June 2006|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/06/25/sports/25iht-web.wcargmex.2040478.html|title=Argentina downs Mexico 2\u20131 in overtime|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=24 June 2006|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> after the departure of manager [[Ricardo La Volpe]], his replacement [[Hugo S\u00e1nchez]] kept the player in his squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lainformacion.com/deporte/guardado-dice-que-para-ser-sucesor-de-hugo-sanchez-hay-que-ser-pichichi-cinco-veces_vqyBeAvnmQWRh64MupdYJ/|title=Guardado dice que \"para ser sucesor de Hugo S\u00e1nchez hay que ser Pichichi cinco veces\"|trans-title=Guardado says that \"in order to succeed Hugo S\u00e1nchez you have to be a Pichichi five times\"|newspaper=La Informaci\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=10 December 2009|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nGuardado's first game under the new manager was an exhibition game against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], where he came on as a [[Substitute (association football)|bench]] in a 0\u20132 defeat.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Mens-National-Team/2007/06/USA-Vs-Mexico-Last-Time-Out-Feb-7-2007.aspx | title = SA vs. Mexico: Last Time Out&nbsp;\u2013 Feb. 7, 2007 | publisher = US Soccer | date = 23 June 2007 | accessdate = 16 February 2014 | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140201235020/http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Mens-National-Team/2007/06/USA-Vs-Mexico-Last-Time-Out-Feb-7-2007.aspx | archive-date = 1 February 2014 | df = dmy-all}}</ref> On 28 February 2007, in a friendly with [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]], he scored his first international goal (3\u20131 win).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/mexico/cronicas/2007/02/28/cronica-mexico-3-1-venezuela_9397 | title = M\u00e9xico 3 \u2013 Venezuela 1: Vistiendo de blanco, El Tri gan\u00f3 su primer duelo con Hugo al frente |trans-title=M\u00e9xico 3 \u2013 Venezuela 1: Wearing white, ''El Tri'' won their first game under Hugo | publisher = Medio Tiempo | language = Spanish | first = Walter | last = Gonz\u00e1lez | date = 28 February 2007 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn [[2007 CONCACAF Gold Cup Final|the final]] of the [[2007 CONCACAF Gold Cup]],<ref name=TRI>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/convocatoria-tri-copa-oro-copa-america|title=Convocatoria del Tri para Copa de Oro y Copa Am\u00e9rica|trans-title=Tri selection for Gold Cup and Copa Am\u00e9rica|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=18 May 2007|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> Guardado scored the opening goal against the United States. During the second half he collided head-on with [[Jonathan Spector]] while both attempted to head the ball, but recovered to play the rest of the match, which ended in a 1\u20132 loss.<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.usatoday.com/sports/soccer/2007-06-24-usa-mexico-goldcup_N.htm | title = U.S. continues dominance vs. Mexico in Gold Cup final | newspaper = [[USA Today]] | first = Mike | last = Dodd | date = 25 June 2007 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> He also participated in [[2007 Copa America|that year]]'s [[Copa Am\u00e9rica]],<ref name=TRI/> scoring the third goal against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in the third-place match.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://espnfc.com/match?id=221082&cc=5739 | title = Uruguay 1\u20133 Mexico: Comeback victory | publisher = ESPN FC | date = 14 July 2007 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[Javier Aguirre]] included Guardado in the roster for the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://digitaldeporte.com/2010/06/lista-de-convocados-de-mexico-para-el-mundial-de-sudafrica/|title=Lista de convocados de M\u00e9xico para el mundial de Sud\u00e1frica|trans-title=Mexico selection for South Africa's World Cup|publisher=Digital Deporte|language=Spanish|date=2 June 2010|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> He assisted [[Rafael M\u00e1rquez]] in the opening game of the World Cup against hosts [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]], in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nj.com/soccer-news/index.ssf/2010/06/south_africa_vs_mexico_live_bl.html | title = South Africa ties Mexico, 1\u20131, in opening match of 2010 World Cup | newspaper = [[The Star-Ledger]] | first = Colin | last = Stephenson | date = 11 June 2010 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> An expected starter, he lacked playing time<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.com.mx/futbol-futbol-nacional-seleccion-mexicana/aguirre-tenia-poca-confianza-en-mi-guardado|title='Aguirre ten\u00eda poca confianza en m\u00ed': Guardado|trans-title='Aguirre did not trust me that much': Guardado|newspaper=[[R\u00e9cord]]|language=Spanish|date=2 January 2018|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref> and appeared in three out of four games, in another last-16 exit at the hands of Argentina.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2010/matches/match_52/default.stm|title=Argentina 3\u20131 Mexico|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Paul|last=Fletcher|date=27 June 2010|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2011, Guardado was called up by [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel de la Torre]] for the [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2011 Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/tri-oro-convocatoria-chepo-copa-oro|title=Tri de oro... Convocatoria del 'Chepo' para Copa Oro|trans-title=Golden tri... 'Chepo' squad for Gold Cup|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=13 May 2011|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> He scored his first brace with the national team during that tournament, in a 4\u20131 win over [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] on 12 June.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/news/newsid=1451370.html | title = Goals galore for Mexico, El Salvador | publisher = FIFA | date = 12 June 2011 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref> He found the net again in [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup Final|the final]] in a 4\u20132 victory over the United States, as Mexico retained the trophy.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/930380/mexico-comeback-secures-gold-cup-win-over-usa?cc=5739 | title = Mexico claim Gold Cup glory | publisher = ESPN FC | date = 25 June 2011 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/26/sports/soccer/in-an-early-2-0-hole-mexico-storms-back-to-win-the-gold-cup.html | title = In an early 2\u20130 hole, Mexico storms back to win the Gold Cup | newspaper = The New York Times | first = Harvey | last = Araton | date = 26 June 2011 | accessdate = 16 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nGuardado made the squad for the [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/oficializa-mexico-lista-y-numeracion-para-confederaciones|title=Oficializa M\u00e9xico lista y numeraci\u00f3n para Confederaciones|trans-title=Mexico make squad and numbers for Confederations official|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=7 June 2013|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> As ''El Tri'' failed to progress from the group stage, he played all three matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/archive/brazil2013/teams/team=43911/statistics.html|title=Mexico \u2013 Statistics|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March 2014, Guardado made his [[FIFA Century Club|100th appearance]] for Mexico, in a friendly with [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/es/news/58/m%C3%A9xico/2014/03/06/4664964/andr%C3%A9s-guardado-cumpli%C3%B3-100-partidos-con-m%C3%A9xico|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado cumpli\u00f3 100 partidos con M\u00e9xico|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado celebrated 100 games with Mexico|publisher=Goal|language=Spanish|date=6 March 2014|accessdate=13 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=RSSSF>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/guardado-intlg.html|title=Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s Guardado \u2013 Century of International Appearance|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|first=Roberto|last=Mamrud|accessdate=19 April 2015}}</ref> Selected by [[Miguel Herrera]] for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]] in Brazil,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/mexico/10810189/Mexico-World-Cup-2014-squad.html|title=Mexico World Cup 2014 squad|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=2 June 2014|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> he started all the games as a left midfielder, and scored in the last group phase fixture against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], a 3\u20131 win;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=255931/match=300186452/match-report.html|title=Mexico beat Croatia to spark Recife fiesta|publisher=FIFA|date=23 June 2014|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> following the end of the tournament, the manager declared the player would captain the following September friendlies with [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]], captaining for instances when actual captain Rafael M\u00e1rquez was absent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxdeportes.com/liga-mx/story/andres-guardado-nuevo-capitan-de-mexico/|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, nuevo capit\u00e1n de M\u00e9xico|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, new captain of Mexico|publisher=Fox Deportes|language=Spanish|date=26 August 2014|accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/liga-mx/andres-guardado-sera-el-nuevo-capitan-del-tri|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado ser\u00e1 el nuevo capit\u00e1n del Tri|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado will be the new ''Tri'' captain|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=28 August 2014|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nGuardado scored six times at the [[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2015 Gold Cup]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/2015/06/13/futbol/futbol_internacional/mexico/1434155080.html|title=Plan A de M\u00e9xico para la Copa de Oro con Chicharito y Vela|trans-title=Mexico plan A for the Gold Cup with Chicharito and Vela|newspaper=Marca|language=Spanish|date=13 June 2015|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://espndeportes.espn.go.com/blogs/index?entryID=2427456&name=espn_datos|title=M\u00e9xico y Guardado mandan en Copa Oro|trans-title=Mexico and Guardado rule the Gold Cup|publisher=ESPN Deportes|first=Rafa|last=Ramos|language=Spanish|date=22 July 2015|accessdate=23 July 2015}}</ref> the first being a first-half effort in a 6\u20130 demolition of [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]] in the group stage<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/usa/deportes/6-0-mexico-goleo-a-cuba-con-hat-trick-de-peralta/50000107-2661166|title=6\u20130. M\u00e9xico gole\u00f3 a Cuba con \"hat trick\" de Peralta|trans-title=6\u20130. M\u00e9xico routed Cuba with Peralta hat-trick|publisher=[[EFE]]|language=Spanish|date=10 July 2015|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref> and the third a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]] in the [[Last-minute goal|last minute]] of [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] in the quarter-final against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] (1\u20130).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/mexico-tops-costa-rica-1-0-gold-cup-023757126--sow.html|title=Mexico tops Costa Rica 1\u20130 in Gold Cup on late penalty|publisher=[[Yahoo Sports]]|date=20 July 2015|accessdate=20 July 2015}}</ref> In the semi-finals against [[Panama national football team|Panama]], he scored twice from the penalty spot to help his country come from behind and win 2\u20131<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/20150723/20960479839/futbol-copa-oro-semifinales-resumen.html|title=Jamaica fue \"David\" ante Estados Unidos y M\u00e9xico gan\u00f3 con pol\u00e9mica arbitral|trans-title=Jamaica was \"David\" against the United States and Mexico won with refereeing controversy|newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=Spanish|date=23 July 2015|accessdate=23 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportingnews.com/soccer/story/2015-07-23/concacaf-gold-cup-mexico-captain-andres-guardado-miss-penalty-kick-pk-penal-on-purpose-panama|title=CONCACAF Gold Cup: Mexico captain Andres Guardado considered missing PK on purpose|publisher=Sporting News|date=23 July 2015|accessdate=23 July 2015}}</ref> and, in [[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup Final|the decisive match]] against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]], scored the opener in an eventual 3\u20131 victory.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/jul/26/mexico-rolls-to-seventh-gold-cup-title-with-uncontroversial-win-over-jamaica|title=Gold Cup 2015 final: Mexico roll to seventh title with easy win over Jamaica|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=27 July 2015|accessdate=27 July 2015}}</ref> Subsequently, he won the Golden Ball Award as most outstanding player.<ref name=\"Golden\">{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/mexicos-guardado-earns-golden-ball-award|title=Mexico's Guardado earns Golden Ball award|publisher=[[CONCACAF]]|date=26 July 2015|accessdate=8 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nPicked for the [[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario]] squad by [[Juan Carlos Osorio]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/mexico-announces-team-for-copa-america-centenario-and-it-looks-scary-good-051716|title=Mexico announces team for Copa America Centenario and it looks scary good|publisher=Fox Sports|date=17 May 2016|accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> Guardado provided a cross in the opening fixture against Uruguay that led to an [[Own goal#Association football|own goal]] but was also [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] for two [[Penalty card#Yellow card|bookable offences]], winning 3\u20131 at [[University of Phoenix Stadium]] on 5 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/06/05/mexico-3-uruguay-1-copa-america-centenario-match-recap|title=Mexico 3, Uruguay 1 Copa America Centenario match recap|publisher=[[Major League Soccer]]|date=5 June 2016|accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2644509-jekyll-and-hyde-mexico-find-a-way-to-see-off-uruguay-and-take-control-of-group-c|title=Jekyll-and-Hyde Mexico find a way to see off Uruguay and take control of Group C|publisher=[[Bleacher Report]]|first=Rob|last=Lancaster|date=6 June 2016|accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> He took part in a further two games, in a quarter-final exit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/mexico/fue-accidental-el-7-0-de-chile-sobre-mexico-en-la-copa-america|title=El 7\u20130 de Chile a M\u00e9xico, \u00bffue un accidente del f\u00fatbol o reflej\u00f3 la realidad de ambas selecciones?|trans-title=Chile's 7\u20130 to Mexico, stuff that happens in football or mirror of both national teams?|publisher=[[TUDN (TV network)|TUDN]]|first=Blanca|last=Luna|language=Spanish|date=15 October 2018|accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nGuardado also made the final list for the [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup|2017 Confederations Cup]] in Russia,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/mexico/mexico-definio-a-los-23-convocados-que-iran-a-la-copa-confederaciones-de-rusia|title=M\u00e9xico defini\u00f3 a los 23 convocados que ir\u00e1n a la Copa Confederaciones de Rusia|trans-title=M\u00e9xico defini\u00f3 a los 23 convocados que ir\u00e1n a la Copa Confederaciones de Rusia|publisher=TUDN|language=Spanish|date=8 June 2017|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> where he appeared as captain in the group stage fixtures against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] and [[Russia national football team|Russia]], picking up a yellow card on both occasions and thus missing out in the semi-finals against [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es-ar/noticias/que-pierde-mexico-sin-andres-guardado/h2jaasrnefoo1qh3hclnl74bi|title=\u00bfQu\u00e9 pierde M\u00e9xico sin Andr\u00e9s Guardado?|trans-title=What are Mexico missing without Andr\u00e9s Guardado?|publisher=Goal|first=Paulo|last=Medina|language=Spanish|date=28 June 2017|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> He returned to the lineup in the third-place playoff, lost 2\u20131 to Portugal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.excelsior.com.mx/adrenalina/2017/07/02/1173214|title=Revive los goles de la derrota de M\u00e9xico ante Portugal|trans-title=Relive goals of Mexico's defeat against Portugal|newspaper=[[Exc\u00e9lsior]]|language=Spanish|date=2 July 2017|accessdate=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Mex-Kor (24).jpg|thumb|Guardado as captain for Mexico at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]]]]\nGuardado was selected in the final 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://miseleccion.mx/convocatoria-la-seleccion-nacional-mexico-13/|title=Convocatoria de la Selecci\u00f3n Nacional de M\u00e9xico|trans-title=Mexico national team call-up|publisher=Mi Selecci\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=4 June 2018|accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> his first as captain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talksport.com/football/379554/mexico-world-cup-2018-team-guide-group-f-opponents-and-fixtures-kits-key-player-probable/|title=GROUP F Mexico World Cup 2018 team guide \u2013 opponents and fixtures, kits, key player, plus probable line-up|publisher=[[Talksport]]|date=17 June 2018|accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> In the first match, he played 74 minutes in a 1\u20130 defeat of Germany,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44427969|title=Germany 0\u20131 Mexico|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Chris|last=Bevan|date=17 June 2018|accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> going on to take part in all the fixtures including the round of 16 loss with [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44597762|title=Brazil 2\u20130 Mexico|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Patrick|last=Jennings|date=2 July 2018|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref> Following their elimination, according to a report by Mexican sports newspaper ''[[R\u00e9cord]]'', he supposedly played through the tournament with an injury.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.com.mx/futbol-futbol-nacional-seleccion-mexicana/andres-guardado-jugo-infiltrado-el-mundial|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado jug\u00f3 infiltrado el Mundial|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado played through pain in World Cup|newspaper=R\u00e9cord|first=Carlos|last=Ponce de Le\u00f3n|language=Spanish|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nGuardado was called up by [[Gerardo Martino]] to participate in the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2019 Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/claro-mx/futbol/seleccion-mx/2019/06/06/5cf8847122601d525a8b45ef.html|title=El Tata Martino da a conocer la lista de la selecci\u00f3n mexicana para la Copa Oro|trans-title=Tata Martino releases Mexican national team list for the Gold Cup|newspaper=Marca|language=Spanish|date=5 June 2019|accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref> In the second [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup Group A|group match]] against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]], he replaced the injured [[\u00c9rick Guti\u00e9rrez]] at the 37th minute and scored twice, helping to a 3\u20131 win and being named [[Player of the match]].<ref name=\"Engine\">{{cite web|url=https://deadspin.com/andres-guardado-is-the-engine-that-makes-mexico-run-at-1835691157|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado is the engine that makes Mexico run at full power|publisher=[[Deadspin]]|first=Luis|last=Paez-Pumar|date=20 June 2019|accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref> He broke various [[CONCACAF]]-based records at the end of that stage, among them the most-capped Mexican player in the Gold Cup and the only from the country to score in four editions of the [[CONCACAF Gold Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/copa-oro/andres-guardado-el-hombre-records-del-tri-en-copa-oro|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, el hombre r\u00e9cords del Tri en Copa Oro|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, the Gold Cup ''Tri'' recordman|publisher=TUDN|first=\u00d3scar|last=Guevara|language=Spanish|date=23 June 2019|accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref> eventually winning the competition and being included in the Best XI.<ref name=BESTXI>{{cite web|url=https://www.goldcup.org/en/awards/2019-concacaf-gold-cup-best-xi|title=2019 Concacaf Gold Cup \u2013 Best XI|publisher=[[CONCACAF Gold Cup]]|date=7 July 2019|accessdate=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nGuardado started his career as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] at Atlas, occasionally playing as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/la-liga/andres-guardado-satisfecho-con-su-labor-como-lateral|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, satisfecho con su labor como lateral|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, happy with full-back role|publisher=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish|date=13 January 2013|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> He was mainly deployed in the former position at Deportivo by [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Lotina]],<ref name=Goal>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es-mx/noticias/la-evolucion-de-guardado-de-carrilero-inagotable-a-cerebro-en-el-/vhq868xp5fip10n9snoa2xfe3|title=La evoluci\u00f3n de Guardado: de carrilero inagotable a cerebro en el mediocampo|trans-title=Guardado's evolution: from tireless wingback to midfield brain|publisher=Goal|first=Jhon|last=Gui\u00f1an|language=Spanish|date=4 October 2018|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> and changed to the latter after moving to Valencia.<ref name=\"Lecture\"/> When played as a winger, he was an incisive and quick footballer, known to play deep into the field, take on defenders one-on-one and provide accurate crosses, managing to score for both club and country.<ref name=Goal/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1943270-scouting-report-bayer-leverkusen-signing-andres-guardado-is-a-transfer-steal|title=Scouting report: Bayer Leverkusen signing Andres Guardado is a transfer steal|publisher=Bleacher Report|first=Allan|last=Jiang|date=31 January 2014|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box|width=33%|align=left|quote=\"[H]e will surely be the best footballer I have trained and that I am going to train in terms of course. He is a footballer with many merits. Not only in the conditions, but in what he creates. When the rest stops, he keeps on running.\"|source=\u2014Former [[Real Betis]] manager [[Quique Seti\u00e9n]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sevilla.abc.es/deportes/alfinaldelapalmera/noticias/real-betis/setien-seguramente-guardado-sera-mejor-jugador-he-entrenado-voy-entrenar-140228-1510593465.html|title=Seti\u00e9n: \u201cSeguramente, Guardado es el mejor jugador que he entrenado y voy a entrenar\u201d|trans-title=Seti\u00e9n: \"Surely, Guardado is the best player I've trained and will train\"|newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|first1=Ram\u00f3n|last1=Rom\u00e1n|first2=M.|last2=Gonz\u00e1lez|first3=Jes\u00fas|last3=Sevillano|first4=Juan|last4=Arbide|language=Spanish|date=13 November 2017|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>}}\n\nIn 2014, under [[Miguel Herrera]]'s improvisation, Guardado began to play as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for the national team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://archivo.eluniversal.com.mx/deportes/2014/impreso/donde-me-pongan-sere-feliz-guardado-155790.html|title=Donde me pongan ser\u00e9 feliz: Guardado|trans-title=Wherever they play me I'll be happy: Guardado|newspaper=El Universal|first=Daniel|last=Blumrosen Ju\u00e1rez|language=Spanish|date=30 May 2014|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/114/mexico/2014/06/02/4854943/tom-marshall-defensive-midfield-options-for-mexico |title=Tom Marshall: Defensive midfield options for Mexico|publisher=Goal|first=Tom|last=Marshall|date=2 June 2014|accessdate=}}</ref> At PSV, manager [[Phillip Cocu]] facilitated his positional change as injuries hampered his speed,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/andres-guardado-magisterial-mexican/|title=Andres Guardado \u2013 The magisterial Mexican|publisher=Football Oranje|first=Chaka|last=Simbeye|date=8 July 2017|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Importance\">{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1987585-assessing-the-importance-of-andres-guardado-to-the-mexico-national-side|title=Assessing the importance of Andres Guardado to the Mexico national side|publisher=Bleacher Report|first=Karla|last=Villegas Gama|date=14 March 2014|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/deportes/Guardado-de-la-rapidez-al-juego-pensado-20180605-0168.html|title=Guardado: de la rapidez al juego pensado|trans-title=Guardado: from speediness to the mindful game|newspaper=[[El Economista (Mexico)|El Economista]]|first=Eduardo|last=Hern\u00e1ndez Castro|language=Spanish|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref> as the latter began to operate as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]] with [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/pro-sports/mexico-andres-guardado-interested-playing-mls/F719FNL7Lu10kOuzG0GRwK/#|title=Mexico\u2019s Andres Guardado interested in playing in MLS|newspaper=[[The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|first=Doug|last=Roberson|date=28 May 2016|accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"FIFA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/guardado-s-mixed-memories-and-enduring-dream-2925716?_branch_match_id=459121624082689116|title=Guardado's mixed memories and enduring dream|publisher=FIFA|date=2 January 2018|accessdate=20 September 2019|quote=I used to be more of a box-to-box player, who took people on and got on the end of moves. Now, I'm a central midfielder and hold my position more; I bring balance to the team.}}</ref> and [[Playmaker#Deep-lying playmakers|deep-lying playmaker]] qualities;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fmfstateofmind.com/2017/5/1/15486532/season-report-andres-guardado|title=Season report: Andres Guardado|publisher=[[SB Nation]]|first=Raul|last=Barraza|date=1 May 2017|accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerpro.com/thecentercircle/the-nations-of-the-21st-world-cup-mexico/|title=The nations of the 21st World Cup \u2013 Mexico|publisher=Soccer Pro|first=James|last=Wilkinson|date=14 May 2018|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref> he later took on more defensive duties.<ref name=\"FIFA\"/><ref name=\"Taught\">{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2015/03/03/futbol/futbol_internacional/mexico/1425390899.html|title=Cocu me ha ense\u00f1ado a jugar de mediocentro|trans-title=\"Cocu has taught me how to play as a central midfielder\"|newspaper=Marca|location=Madrid|language=Spanish|date=3 March 2015|accessdate=14 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.excelsior.com.mx/adrenalina/andres-guardado-el-hombre-sin-miedo/1245253|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, el hombre sin miedo|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, the fearless man|newspaper=Exc\u00e9lsior|language=Spanish|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=14 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/players/player/251352/profile/|title=Andres GUARDADO|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=20 September 2019|quote=The midfielder began his career stationed on the left flank, where he got himself noticed with his speed and long-range shooting skills. As his career developed, he shifted to central midfield and now performs more defensive duties.}}</ref>\n\nA creative player with excellent vision,<ref name=\"Importance\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2017/12/04/andrs-guardado-can-the-little-prince-lift-leeds-up/|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado: can the little prince lift Leeds up?|publisher=HITC|first=Muhammad|last=Butt|date=4 December 2017|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref> Guardado is also a technically proficient player known for establishing the tempo of his team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2018/08/21/mexicos-andres-guardado-mulls-mls-move-notes-good-contract-offer|title=Mexico's Andres Guardado mulls MLS move, notes \"good contract\" offer|publisher=[[Major League Soccer]]|first=Charles|last=Boehm|date=21 August 2018|accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> He also has good passing and [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, also being proficient at [[Direct free kick|free kicks]] and holding up the ball. He also possesses a powerful and accurate shot from distance, and is also capable of aiding his team defensively due to his [[work rate]] and stamina;<ref name=\"Taught\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/es-mx/news/4947/f%C3%BAtbol-internacional/2015/05/10/11607882/andr%C3%A9s-guardado-de-principito-a-rey|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, \u00bfde Principito a Rey?|trans-title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado, from Little Prince to King?|publisher=Goal|language=Spanish|date=10 May 2015|accessdate=1 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2016/03/08/portada/1457430163_974749.html|title=Los 11 'jugadores reconvertidos' m\u00e1s importantes de la Liga|trans-title=La Liga's 11 most important 'reconverted players'|newspaper=[[Diario AS]]|first=Edu|last=Herrero|language=Spanish|date=8 March 2016|accessdate=1 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Players/21019|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado|publisher=Who Scored|date=29 March 2016}}</ref> additionally, he was described as playing closer to the \"Iberian midfielder archetype,\" focused on possession in the center of the field, winning the ball back with smart positioning instead of tackles and then pushing it forward.<ref name=\"Engine\"/>\n\nGuardado idolised his compatriot and national teammate Rafael M\u00e1rquez, citing him as an influence in his playing style.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://somosinvictos.com/2016/03/27/admiracion-total-herrera-torrado-vela-y-guardado-explican-lo-que-representa-jugar-con-rafa-marquez|title=Admiraci\u00f3n total: Herrera, Torrado, Vela y Guardado explican lo que representa jugar con Rafa M\u00e1rquez|trans-title=Total admiration: Herrera, Torrado, Vela and Guardado explain what it means to play with Rafa M\u00e1rquez|publisher=Somos Invictos|language=Spanish|date=27 March 2016|accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/claro-mx/futbol/seleccion-mx/entrevistas/2018/05/10/5af33d09e2704e9b158b4688.html|title=Guardado: \"Rafa M\u00e1rquez es un espejo en el cual siempre me he tratado de reflejar\"|trans-title=Guardado: \"Rafa M\u00e1rquez is a mirror in which I always try to reflect myself off\"|newspaper=Marca|language=Spanish|date=10 May 2018|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGuardado married fellow Guadalajara native Briana Morales in December 2006. Five years later, they divorced.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oLaZDAAAQBAJ&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Andr\u00e9s Guardado|first=Jorge Arturo|last=Miranda Bravo|publisher=Mason Crest|date=2013|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGuardado is an \"honorary associate\" of the ''Asociaci\u00f3n Mexicana de Futbolistas'' (Mexican Footballers Association), created in October 2017. An association that its main goal is, according to him, to \"create a dialogue with league, federation and club authorities\" with the domestic league's footballers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amfpro.mx/comunicados-amfpro/nace-asociacion/|title=Nace la Asociaci\u00f3n Mexicana de Futbolistas|trans-title=Mexican Footballers Association is born|publisher=Mexican Footballers Association|language=Spanish|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=12 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/mexico/story/3223712/chicharito-backs-new-mexican-footballers-association|title=Chicharito throws support behind new Mexican footballers' association|publisher=[[ESPN]]|first=Tom|last=Marshall|date=8 October 2017|accessdate=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nMuch of Guardado's first year at Betis' [[Estadio Benito Villamar\u00edn]] was captured in the [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime]] television documentary series ''Six Dreams'', in which he was one of the stars.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://en.as.com/en/2018/03/08/football/1520517172_303503.amp.html|title=Six Dreams: Amazon launch series following LaLiga stars lives|newspaper=Diario AS|first=Rafael|last=Garc\u00eda Dom\u00ednguez|date=8 March 2018|accessdate=27 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 8 March 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jose-andres-guardado-hernandez/425/|title=A. Guardado|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{ESPN FC|76932}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Club Atlas|Atlas]]\n|[[2005 Primera Divisi\u00f3n de M\u00e9xico Apertura|2005]]\u2013[[Primera Divisi\u00f3n de M\u00e9xico Clausura 2006|06]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Liga MX|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n|26||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||26||1\n|-\n|[[Primera Divisi\