he government's plan to create an Economic Analysis and Business Facilitation Unit\n|accessdate=2008-08-12\n|last=\n|first=\n| date=14 April 2004\n}}\n</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100523133146/http://www.eabfu.gov.hk/ Economic Analysis and Business Facilitation Unit] {{in lang|en}} {{in lang|zh-hk}} {{in lang|zh}}\n{{Government of Hong Kong}}\n{{Financial Secretary (Hong Kong)}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Economic Analysis And Business Facilitation Unit}}\n[[Category:Hong Kong government departments and agencies]]\n[[Category:Ministries established in 2004]]\n\n\n{{HongKong-gov-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=May 2008}}\n{{Use Hong Kong English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name   = Office of the Government Economist\n|nativename    = \n|nativename_a  = \u653f\u5e9c\u7d93\u6fdf\u9867\u554f\u8fa6\u516c\u5ba4\n|nativename_r  = \n|logo          = Hong Kong SAR Regional Emblem.svg\n|logo_width    = 140px\n|logo_caption  = Emblem of the Hong Kong SAR\n|seal          = \n|seal_width    = \n|seal_caption  = \n|formed        = 2004\n|preceding1    = \n|preceding2    = \n|dissolved     = \n|superseding   = \n|jurisdiction  = \n|headquarters  = [[Central, Hong Kong]]\n|coordinates   = \n|employees     = \n|budget        = \n|minister1_name  = [[Paul Chan Mo-po|Paul Chan]]\n|minister1_pfo   = [[Financial Secretary]]\n|minister2_name  = \n|minister2_pfo   = \n|chief1_name     = Andrew Au\n|chief1_position = Government Economist\n|chief2_name     = \n|chief2_position = \n|parent_agency = [[Financial Secretary's Office]]\n|child1_agency = \n|child2_agency = \n|child3_agency = \n|child4_agency = \n|child5_agency = \n|child6_agency = \n|child7_agency = \n|child8_agency = \n|website       = [http://www.eabfu.gov.hk/ www.eabfu.gov.hk/]\n|footnotes     = \n}}\n\nThe '''Office of the Government Economist''' (OGE) of the [[Hong Kong]] government was formed under the Financial Secretary\u2019s Office on 1 June 2004, when the [[HKSAR]] Government merged the Economic Analysis Division (under the Financial Services Branch of the Financial Services and the Treasury Bureau) and the Business Facilitation Division (previously under the Commerce and Industry Branch of the Commerce, Industry and Technology Bureau).<ref>\n{{cite news\n|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-21002539_ITM\n|title=Rumpus over WTO jobs. |publisher= Asia Africa Intelligence Wire (April, 2004)\n|quote= Meanwhile, lawmakers were generally supportive of the government's plan to create an Economic Analysis and Business Facilitation Unit\n|accessdate=2008-08-12\n|last=\n|first=\n| date=14 April 2004\n}}\n</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100523133146/http://www.eabfu.gov.hk/ Economic Analysis and Business Facilitation Unit] {{in lang|en}} {{in lang|zh-hk}} {{in lang|zh}}\n{{Government of Hong Kong}}\n{{Financial Secretary (Hong Kong)}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Economic Analysis And Business Facilitation Unit}}\n[[Category:Hong Kong government departments and agencies]]\n[[Category:Ministries established in 2004]]\n\n\n{{HongKong-gov-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economic_Analysis_and_Business_Facilitation_Unit"}
